cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on computer vision and deep learning techniques for object recognition, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the use of a recurrent architecture and attention mechanism suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) for optimization suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the use of the Spatial Transformer for geometric transformation suggests that it may also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category.
